title: rustc 1.30.0 - ICE on `cargo doc --open` with `typenum` crate
body:
Internal Compiler Error when running `cargo doc --open` on macOS Mojave

I tried this code:

```
extern crate flate2;
extern crate rusoto_core;
extern crate rusoto_s3;
extern crate serde_json;

use rusoto_core::Region;
use rusoto_s3::{ListObjectsRequest, S3, S3Client};

fn main() {
    // ...
}
```

I expected to see this happen:

`cargo doc --open` should build the project's docs and open mah default browser (Firefox Developer Edition).

Instead, this happened:

Internal Compiler Error

## Meta

`rustc --version --verbose`:

```
rustc 1.30.0 (da5f414c2 2018-10-24)
binary: rustc
commit-hash: da5f414c2c0bfe5198934493f04c676e2b23ff2e
commit-date: 2018-10-24
host: x86_64-apple-darwin
release: 1.30.0
LLVM version: 8.0
```

Backtrace:

```
 Documenting typenum v1.10.0
 Documenting hyper v0.12.13
    Checking rusoto_credential v0.13.0
    Checking hyper-tls v0.3.1
    Checking rusoto_core v0.34.0
error: internal compiler error: librustc/traits/structural_impls.rs:178: impossible case reached

error: Could not document `typenum`.

Caused by:
  process didn't exit successfully: `rustdoc --crate-name typenum /Users/davidlewis/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/typenum-1.10.0/src/lib.rs --cap-lints allow --color always -o '/Users/davidlewis/...' -L 'dependency=/Users/davidlewis/...'` (exit code: 1)
warning: build failed, waiting for other jobs to finish...
error: build failed
```
